Job Opportunities

   More than 23 million jobs -- 17 percent of the civilian workforce --
   are involved in some facet of American agriculture, making it the
   Nation's largest employer. The Risk Management Agency's (RMA's) job is
   to help ensure that farmers, on whom all this depends, have the
   financial tools necessary to manage their agricultural risks. In 2000,
   we provided farmers over $34 billion in coverage through more than 1.9
   million policies sold by about 15,000 agents and 18 insurance
   companies.

Current RMA Job Opportunities

     * Senior Actuary (SL-1510-00/00) -- Location of position: Kansas
       City, MO. Closes February 20, 2002.
       OF-612 - Optional Application for Federal Employment.

     * Risk Management Assistant (GS-1101-05/06) -- Location of position:
       Springfield, IL. Closes February 01, 2002.

Other USDA Employment Listings

     * U.S. Department of Agriculture -- Search for USDA jobs. (Also see
       the USAJOBS-by-Phone telephone service.)
     * USDA's Summer Intern Program (SIP) -- Open to currently enrolled
       college students who are pursuing further education. Application
       instructions and information concerning the disciplines are
       included. The SIP provides an opportunity for students to work as
       assistants to scientific, professional, and technical employees.
       These positions provide students a paid, summer intern experience
       and information about career opportunities and future employment
       prospects at USDA.

   Employment Listings from Our Mission Area (Farm and Foreign
   Agricultural Service-FFAS)
     * Foreign Agriculture Service (FAS) -- The Foreign Agricultural
       Service regularly recruits professionals with backgrounds in
       agriculture, economics, marketing and other related disciplines to
       fill vacancies as the need arises.
     * Farm Service Agency (FSA) -- This link provides an online form to
       select current job opportunities within FSA and USDA. The data is
       derived from OPM's database.

